{
  "stem": "16245.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now I remember American planes dropping leaflets that 600,000 Jews were gassed in Auschwitz and obviously threatening people-- it was a message from President Roosevelt-- threatening people with war crimes after the war, that they'll be punished after the war, and threatening rewards for those who will help Jews.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember my father and I picking up a leaflet and neither of us believed it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there were a couple of escapees in Budapest from Auschwitz who were brought out before the German occupation by the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And nobody really believed their story.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, you have to think about it that even today it's difficult to believe.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, you know it's there, but that it was there, and it's difficult to believe.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean for us, it was better not to believe it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And of course, the Germans did everything possible to camouflage it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "For instance, a lot of the Jews from the country, relations of ours, sent a postcard from Auschwitz with a postmark named [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Now you looked at the map, [GERMAN] was right next to the Swiss border.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And straight after they wrote the card and they said, what a wonderful trip they had, how well they were treated, and all that, they went straight to the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't really remember, but because there was a war on, we had quite a bit of food salted away.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "People in those days had pantries.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was no shopping as we know it today.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You didn't have to go to the shops every day.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had sacks full of sugar, salt and cooking fat and that sort of thing stashed away.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The daily shopping, I really don't remember how it was done.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
